---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

export const prerender = true;

// Toggle this to true after Margaret's review and approval call.
const margaretApproved = false;
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About · America's School Trust Library"
  description="A working library for the school trust lands — the 77 million acres set aside, beginning in 1785, to fund public education in perpetuity."
  sourceId="about-page"
>
  <article class="prose prose-slate max-w-none prose-a:text-blue-700 prose-a:underline">
    {/* v9 D.2 — small header mark for the Library seal. Library Mode
        only; image lands later (Cowork-side). onerror handler keeps
        the placeholder invisible until the asset is dropped in. */}
    <p class="library-seal-header-wrap" aria-hidden="true">
      <img
        src="/seal/library-seal-v1.png"
        alt=""
        class="library-seal library-seal--header"
        onerror="this.style.display='none'"
      />
    </p>

    <p class="kicker">About</p>
    <h1>About America's School Trust Library</h1>

    <p>
      America's School Trust Library is a working library for the school trust lands — the 77 million acres set aside, beginning in 1785, to fund public education in perpetuity. Most Americans have never heard of these lands. The Library collects the law, history, financial records, and case material that show what was promised, what was done, and what is owed. Our readers are state trust officials, legislators, journalists, scholars, teachers, and the children and grandchildren of the beneficiaries.
    </p>

    <h2>A joint project</h2>

    <p>
      The Library is run by two affiliated nonprofits. <strong>Advocates for School Trust Lands (ASTL)</strong> is the national organization (<a href="https://schooltrustlands.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">schooltrustlands.org</a>). <strong>Oregon Advocates for School Trust Lands (OASTL)</strong> is the Oregon affiliate (<a href="https://oastl.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oastl.org</a>) and the lead plaintiff in the standing case now before Oregon's appellate courts. The two organizations share staff, source material, and editorial direction.
    </p>

    <h2>Who runs the Library</h2>

    <p>
      <strong>Margaret Bird</strong> is President of ASTL and co-author of the Library's encyclopedia of state trust histories. She is the national domain authority on school trust lands and has spent her career inside and alongside the state offices that administer them.
    </p>

    <p>
      <strong>Dave Sullivan</strong> is President of OASTL and lead plaintiff in the Oregon standing case. He is a retired professor and tree farmer who came to this work after a long career in systems and education.
    </p>

    <p>
      The Library's day-to-day building — cataloging, drafting, design, the back-end — is carried out in partnership with Claude, an AI system serving as architect and librarian. How that partnership works is described in <a href="/about/how-this-works/">How the Library Works</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>Contact and corrections</h2>

    <p>
      The Library expects to be wrong sometimes, and asks readers to help fix it. Anywhere on the site, use the <strong>Submit Feedback</strong> and <strong>Submit Correction</strong> controls to send a note tied to the page you are reading. A Library Card (free) lets you track your submissions and our responses. The longer walkthrough is at <a href="/about/contributing/">Contributing</a>.
    </p>

    <p>
      For institutional contact: ASTL at <a href="https://schooltrustlands.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">schooltrustlands.org</a>, OASTL at <a href="https://oastl.org" target="_blank" rel="noopener">oastl.org</a>. The argument for why a library is the right institutional form for this work is laid out in <a href="/reading/sacred-compact/">The Eighth Anchor</a>. For governance, see <a href="/pro/governance/">Governance</a>; for what we collect, see <a href="/pro/collection-development/">What the Library Collects</a>; for editorial practice, see <a href="/pro/editorial-standards/">Editorial Standards</a>.
    </p>

    <hr class="archival-divider">

    <section class={`signature-block ${margaretApproved ? 'approved' : 'pending'}`}>
      <p class="signature-margaret">
        <span class="name">Margaret Bird</span><br>
        <span class="role">President, Advocates for School Trust Lands</span>
        {!margaretApproved && <span class="pending-note"><em>Pending review and sign-off.</em></span>}
      </p>
      <p class="signature-dave">
        <span class="name">Dave Sullivan</span><br>
        <span class="role">President, Oregon Advocates for School Trust Lands</span>
      </p>
    </section>
  </article>

  <style>
    .kicker {
      font-family: var(--font-sans);
      font-size: 0.72rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      letter-spacing: 0.1em;
      text-transform: uppercase;
      color: #A88A4E;
      margin: 0 0 0.4rem;
    }
  </style>
</BaseLayout>
